      "matters": "Report Of Status Of Administration<br>Off Calendar Dec-17-2007 Continued To Feb-04-08 At 09:00 A.M. In Dept 204<br>MINI MINUTES: APPEARANCES- CLAUDE L. LOWEN, EXECUTOR IN PRO PER;<br><br>MR. LOWEN REPORTED TO THE COURT THAT THE ESTATE IS NOT READY FOR FINAL DISTRIBUTION DUE TO LACK OF FORMAL RECEIPT OF ESTATE TAX CLOSING LETTER.   THE COURT INDICATED THAT THE PETITION FOR FINAL DISTRIBUTION CAN REQUEST A CASH RESERVE FOR CLOSING TAXES OR TO COVER ANY ADDITIONAL ESTATE TAXES WHICH MAY BE INCURRED UPON ANY AUDIT OR PENDING RECEIPT OF THE ESTATE TAX CLOSING LETTER.  THE COURT APPROVED THE STATUS REPORT.  THE COURT CONTINUED THE MATTER TO FEBRUARY 4, 2008 FOR THE STATUS OF THE FILING OF THE PETITION FOR FINAL DISTRIBUTION.<br><br>Judge Pro Tem: Dorothy L. McMath. Reporter: KAREN FARNSWORTH CSR #5162. Clerk: Cynthia Herbert  Bailiff: Deputy Leung",
